Package: kflc
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, build-essential
Recommends: libk26astro-core-dev (= ${source:Version}),
 libk26m3d-dev (= ${source:Version})
Description: KFL programming language compiler
 KFL is a scope-oriented language with arena allocation, own/borrow/ptr
 qualifiers, and built-in bindings for the K26 numerical library suite.
 .
 kflc parses .kfl source and emits a C++ intermediate that is then
 compiled by the system C++ toolchain. The compiler itself depends only
 on libc. Consumers of its output need a C/C++ toolchain plus whichever
 K26 libraries the .kfl source references.

Package: libk26util0
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: KFL stack utilities (runtime)
 General-purpose C utilities for the KFL stack: string helpers exposed
 to KFL's expression layer, POSIX filesystem primitives, and atomic
 file I/O.

